            <bug_when>2009-12-11 16:13:38 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The fix looks ok, although it&#39;s not clear to me why the issue came up in the 
first place. I can think of translated strings in one locale that are &quot;sticky&quot; 
when the next processed locale doesn&#39;t have them (which usually doesn&#39;t happen 
as all message id&#39;s should equally be in all .po files!?). My feeling is this 
can only happen in .po files that are highly divergent, which cannot happen 
when they are generated by the generator, IMO.

The fix is a step back in performance, as the getPotFile() method is expensive. 
Maybe this should be reviewed for performance issues at a later time.

Down prio and to 1.0.1.</thetext>
